description: Our second ride of the season! This is a 16km ride along the E&N and the Goose, starting in Vic West, through Saanich, a bit of View Royal, and back to Vic Fest, ending at Vic Fest West, WHICH has a beer garden. We will meet at Deadman's Junction at 12:00 p.m., which is on the Vic West side of the trestle that crosses the Gorge. We will wait 10 minutes for stragglers and then head out. We will have rest spots along the way for a water and high-five break. We finish at Banfield Park for a group beer. DISCLAIMER: This group is for casual, social bike rides and post-ride meetups. By participating in any ride or event organized here, you acknowledge that you are doing so voluntarily and at your own risk. The organizers and members are not responsible for any injuries, accidents, or damages that may occur during rides or related activities. Please ride safely, obey all traffic laws, and wear appropriate safety gear (like a helmet). You are solely responsible for your own bike, health, and actions. If you choose to drink alcohol after the ride, please do so responsibly and never ride under the influence. Let’s keep it fun and safe for everyone!
location: 800 Tyee RD, VICTORIA, BC, V9A7J2, CA

description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

description: Tango weekend with Jorge Olguín. Saturday, 17th 5pm-6pm solo technique all levels. ( no partner required) Please bring elastic bands!! 6.30pm-7.30pm for couples only ( need some experience) Sacadas, barridas and colgadas in an elastic embrace in order to create a circular movement. We will work with different orchestras to study the changes we need to do to introduce different tempos and rhythms. Get ready for a workout with musicality! 8pm milonga !!! Join us even if you didn’t take the classes. DJ Ingrid !! Free for people registered for the workshops. $10 for drop-ins. Sunday, 18th 11am-12pm solo technique all levels ( no partner required) 12.30pm-1.30pm for couples only ( need some experience ). We will continue with Saturday topic. We will push for more , go deeper , laugh more . Per person: $20 / technique class $25/ partnered workshop $80 entire weekend To register please contact Grazyna ( grazs@shaw.ca or text me or just talk to me ) Private lessons available- register with Grazyna Next workshop dates are June 21st & 22nd Thank you See less Victoria, British Columbia Alive Tango Victoria 1303 Broad St. , Victoria Alive Tango offers practicas, milongas, and classes, special events, and workshops with guest instructors in Victoria BC.
location: Alive Tango Victoria, 1303 Broad St., Victoria
price: $20 / technique class, $25/ partnered workshop, $80 entire weekend

description: Welcome to Dance Temple! Conscious dance and community connection in sacred space. Join us at Edelweiss Club for an ecstatic dance journey ~ Sunday, June 1st features Shauna Devlin as our facilitator/dj! Doors open at 10:45am Dance from 11am to 12:30pm (guided opening at 11). Dance Temple is a weekly Sunday offering. Newcomers welcome! No experience necessary. Please attend only if you feel 100% well. Regular Temple Guidelines (please read through, especially if you're new to Dance Temple): **SHIRTS ON PLEASE** Please keep your shirt on, regardless of your gender. ** IF YOU INTEND TO SWEAT ** Please care for yourself and others by: 1) Taking a shower before you arrive 2) Bringing a towel to wipe up any wake you leave behind **SCENT-FREE SPACE** Please refrain from wearing anything scented in the space. ** CELL PHONE USE ** No cell phone use in the dance space. ** DANCING & CONSENT ** Enjoy your own personal dance or spark up creative movement with others, if there is mutual agreement. ** TALKING ** The dance space is a no-talking zone. ** KIDS ** Parents are asked to kindly monitor their kids and keep them close. **FOOTWEAR** Please wear socks or indoor shoes/sneakers in the dance space. Dance Temple is an inclusive community that celebrates gender diversity and authentic expression. Please arrive early or on time so that we may all journey together. Bring a water bottle. Breathe. Take care of yourself, others and the space. Wear comfortable clothing for movement. Be prepared to sweat.
location: Edelweiss Club, 108 Niagara St, Victoria, BC
price: $20-$40 (no charge for kids under 12); $15-$20 low income

event_name: Milo Walker Johnson Quintet at Little Fernwood
description: Live concert performance at Little Fernwood (Paul Phillips Hall) - Milo Walker Johnson. Exploring the intersection between jazz and classical chamber music, Milo Walker Johnson's original music is inspired by artists like Duke Ellington, Django Reinhardt and Claude Debussy—channeling the musical traditions of swing era jazz and impressionist classical composition. Performed with his fabulous quintet, Milo's compositions offer up a sound and vibe that is cinematic and tender, driving and energetic, all woven through with lush harmonies and creative instrumental textures.
location: 1909 Fernwood RD, VICTORIA, BC, V8T2Y6, CA

description: Class Description This class is for experienced dancers and performers that want to continue to push themselves with more complex techniques. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Monday from 8:00- 9:00pm Must have instructor permission to attend. No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description: We are pleased to offer the Second Annual Tango Marathon in Nelson BC Canada, to be held June 13-15, 2025. This 3 day event will be in one of Western Canada's prettiest and artsiest small towns. Registration is by individual or pair, no partner required. However, we will strive for role balance at this event, so we recommend signing up with a partner. The intention for this event is to create a fabulous series of Milongas, with generous food and drink offerings, and a warm atmosphere of mutual inclusion and respect. We seek to honor the codigos and traditions of Argentine Tango and to create an atmosphere of camaraderie and togetherness. All Tango styles are welcome as long as good floorcraft and consideration for others is maintained. So looking forward to sharing our little town and big hearts with you! We have a lot of great moments mapped out for you on this weekend, Prize draws, group meals, parties, and some fun ice-breaker activities during registration times before the opening Milonga on Friday and throughout the weekend Passes and more info: www.nelsonbctango.com . If you are new to Tango Marathons, the idea is simple: it's like a festival except that instead of focusing on classes, we focus on the Milongas and time on the floor spent dancing. Nelson BC boasts an impressive array of cafes and restaurants, BC's best natural foods co-op, myriad funky and eclectic shops and boutiques, as well as endless hikes and biking trails. For more about Nelson BC, click on this link to the City's website: https://www.nelson.ca/488/About-Nelson
location: 703 Stromme LANE, NELSON, BC, V1L6H7, CA

description: This is our last dance until September, so come help us get ready for summer fun on June 14th in Burnaby with some old school blues and funky, soulful, blues-adjacent music. The night will start with a lesson suitable for beginners as well as experienced dancers, and will move into a DJ’d social dance for the rest of the evening. Doors open at 7:30. Lesson at 7:45 to 8:45. Dance at 8:45 to 11:30. This studio is across the street from the Gilmore Skytrain station for easy transit and there is also free parking available on site. Please wear slidey dance shoes or socks in the studio – heels are not permitted as they will damage the Marley floor and bare feet will probably be uncomfortable. event_name: Texture Your Moves for West Coast Swing
description: We will guide you through practical musicality and movement drills that will 'colour in' any pattern in your repertoire. You'll learn: +++ How you can do more styling without feeling inhibited OR being reckless. +++ How to preserve your partnership connection while still expressing yourself. +++ How to enjoy being musical even with partners who are missing skills. +++ How to respect the rules of the WCS while learning to bend them. Come learn a super practical & universal way to LEVEL UP your musicality by adding body pulse & groove to add more personality and creativity into basic patterns, then get lots of reps to practice these tactics with the appropriate connection and timing. All the while putting these skills to use immediately in your social dancing!
location: 516 Quadra St, Victoria, BC V8V 3S3, Canada
price: $30 via etransfer (for 2hr workshop) $40 (if paying at the door.)

event_name: Mix & Match competition and DJ Nomad at Rhythm City Strut
description: Introducing free, fierce and friendly monthly competitions at Strut! No need to register in advance, no competition fees: just show up at the dance, and step forward when we call for competitors! It's a fun way to challenge yourself, show off what you've been working on, and explore new partnerships. We start with a classic Mix & Match competition. What is a Mix & Match? Simply sign up as a lead or a follow and you'll get randomly paired with dancers of the other role. It's mostly about having fun and doing your best with your partner and the music! This week your DJ is DJ Nomad (Lawrence Chan), with comps music from DJ Monsieur O (Jean-Michel Oblette). ADMISSION FREE for all current Swing 1, Swing 2, Queer Intro To Swing and ELEF Intro To Swing students. • $5 for all other RCP and UBC Swing Club students. • $10 at the door • Free admission if you've never danced before - bring your non-dance friends and we'll show them the basics! • No one turned away for lack of funds. Message us or sign up for a volunteer shift at the door!
source: Strictly Lindy Hop Swing Vancouver, BC | Facebook
location: 2474 Prince Edward St, Vancouver, BC, Canada, British Columbia V5T 1W8

description:
Rehearsal for our Student Bachata Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description:
Rehearsal for our Ladies Team. Open to team members by audition only. Team Description
Auditioned performance groups with rehearsals twice a week plus additional class and social requirements. The group has performed locally as well as in Puerto Rico, New York, Atlanta, Seattle and Chicago. By audition only. Open to team members by audition only. Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.

Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. description: Salsa Del Barrio is a radio show featuring interviews with local and international Salsa dancers and musicians, the history of Salsa music and dance and lots of great Salsa music!

Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

description: Class Description This class is dancers that have completed the Fundamentals course and want to continue to improve their social dancing using the techniques they have learned. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

Auditioned performance groups with rehearsals twice a week plus additional class and social requirements. The group has performed locally as well as in Puerto Rico, New York, Atlanta, Seattle and Chicago. By audition only. Open to team members by audition only. Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description:
Rehearsal for our Student Salsa Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

event_name: Get To Know 2-hour workshop: Intro to Salsa
description: New to Salsa? Baza's Get To Know (GTK) 2-hour Intro to Salsa workshop is perfect for you! NEXT GTK Salsa: Sat, June 21, 12:30-2:30pm. Our GTK sessions are a chance for you to Get To Know the dance, Get To Know our lovely instructors and Get To Know Baza and the amazing vibes here! These special Intro drop-in lessons are catered to Absolute Beginners. We know starting on your dance journey can be a bit scary at first or intimidating, which is why these sessions are a perfect place to start. The pace will be nice and slow, allowing you to wet your feet in the dance without feeling too overwhelmed. You will learn the very basics of the dance which will allow you to feel more confident heading into our Level 1 classes. Most of our students are here to have fun, mingle and get into Social dancing in this amazing community! No experience is necessary! These 2-hour bootcamps are catered for those new to latin social dancing, and perfect for beginner dancers who wish to have a solid refresher on the basics. Open to all dancers of all ages, backgrounds, and skill levels, signing up with a partner is not required as leads and follows will rotate (change partners) throughout the workshop.
source: Beginner Latin Dance and Fitness Classes in Downtown Vancouver
location: Baza Dance Studio

event_name: Mon Salsa Intro (Lvl 1) 7-week Course at 6:15pm starts Jul 7
description: Welcome to Baza! Baza Dance Studio's Salsa Intro course is for absolute beginners and those new to Salsa dancing. There are no pre-requisites for this course and you do not have to have your own partner to enroll. NEXT 7-week Progressive Course on Mondays starts Mon, Jul 7. Class dates: Jul 7, 14, 21, 28, Aug 11, 18 & 25. Class takes place on Mondays from 6:15 - 7:15pm. We also offer this course on Thursdays at 6:15pm and Saturdays at 11:15am. *Make-up classes available. Ultimate Access Members have access to this course but must commit to the entire 6 weeks. *This is a partner dancing class but students are not required to register with a partner. All students will be partnered up with a fellow student or one of our friendly helpers. Dancers have the option to rotate during the class so everyone has a chance to dance with everyone. Instructor: Nupur

description: Come join BC Swing Victoria for a fabulous (and FREE) evening of fun and West Coast Swing dancing at Centennial Square! The schedule for the night will be: 6pm (sharp) there will be an intro lesson to West Coast Swing. 7 - 9pm WCS music will be provided by DJ Carolyn Gebbie. Note: For those who are familiar with the 2019 WCS Rally routine, and would like to practice performing it live prior to Sept 7, the 'Hands Up' song will be played at 7:30 and 8:30pm. There will be WCS instructors on hand to answer questions about WCS or how to improve your WCS dancing.
location: Centennial Square, Victoria, British Columbia

description: Foundation Class (6:30–7:35 PM) Perfect for absolute beginners or dancers looking to strengthen their foundation! In this class, we’ll break down the essential steps, body movement, and partner connection in a fun environment. You’ll learn the basics with proper technique while also adding styling to make your dancing look and feel smooth on the dance floor. No experience or partner needed—just bring your curiosity and energy! Intermediate Class (7:35–8:40 PM) Ready to level up? This class is designed for dancers who already feel comfortable with the basics and want to challenge themselves. We’ll dive into more fun patterns while also exploring musicality—how to connect those movements to the music in a more expressive way. Get ready to build confidence, fluidity, and your own unique style! To Register: Send your e-transfer to maximumotion@gmail.com and include in the memo: Foundation, Intermediate, or Both + Lead or Follow. Class Cancellation & Refunds: We understand that plans can change. However, due to limited spots, renting space in advance, and the preparation required for each class, we’re unable to offer refunds for cancellations. Please make sure you’re committed before signing up. We truly appreciate your understanding and support!
location: 111 Superior St, Victoria, BC V8V 1T2, Canada

See less Victoria, British Columbia Centennial Square Victoria Centennial Square is a plaza in Victoria, British Columbia, Canada. It was built to celebrate the 100th anniversary of the incorporation of the City of Victoria. The Victoria Police Station, city hall and McPherson Playhouse are adjacent to the square. There is a fountain in the square.In the summer, the city hires musicians to perform every weekday, charging no admission fee. For the British Columbia Day holiday, Centennial Square is one of the venues for the Victoria Electronic Music Festival, where musicians and DJs play for free.In the winter, the Downtown Victoria Business Association has temporarily set up Christmas lights, a Ferris wheel, and an ice skating rink in the square.In 2011, Occupy Victoria protesters camped in the square until a court, at the behest of the city, ordered them to leave.

description: Join us for MABUHAY! — a joyful celebration of Filipino Heritage Month, where we invite everyone to experience the vibrant spirit, rich traditions, and warm hospitality of the Filipino community right here in Victoria! This two-day cultural festival will feature: A bustling Food Market with authentic Filipino eats Arts & Crafts Market showcasing local talent Lively Cultural Shows & Exhibits Karaoke, Games, Kids Activities And Live Performances that bring our heritage to life! Why Filipino Heritage Month? Every June, Canada officially recognizes Filipino Heritage Month, celebrating the invaluable contributions of Filipino Canadians to the country’s multicultural fabric. It’s a time to honour our community’s history, culture, achievements, and the joyful spirit of Bayanihan — the tradition of communal unity and cooperation. Who We Are Hosted by the Philippine Bayanihan Community Centre, this event is our way of sharing Filipino culture and heartfelt hospitality with our neighbors and friends across communities. We’re proud to collaborate with the Victoria Filipino Canadian Association (VFCA), Victoria Filipino Canadian Caregivers Association (VFCCA), and Victoria Filipino Canadian Seniors Association (VFCSA). This celebration is proudly supported by: The Province of British Columbia, City of Victoria, and the BC Ferry and Marine Workers' Union. Let’s come together to eat, dance, sing, and celebrate community — Filipino-style! Mark your calendars and bring the whole family! For inquiries, please email us at mabuhay.celebration@gmail.com and admin@bayanihan.ca.
location: Centennial Square, Victoria, BC

description: SpoKizomba is a cozy, all-in-one retreat for Kizomba lovers taking place in Spokane, Washington from August 15–17, 2025. Join us for: • Hands-on workshops with instructor Ashby Laine focused on Kizomba technique, musicality, and embodiment. • Three social dances (two in the evening and one during the day) featuring Kizomba, Semba, Zouk, Ghetto Zouk, and more, with music by DJ Kalcidony and DJ Mario. • Special excursions thoughtfully planned for summertime fun and great community vibes. • Wellness activities and excursions to help you rest and recharge. • Shared meals from Friday dinner through Sunday lunch. • Optional onsite lodging to keep things as simple as possible. SpoKizomba is small by design (capped at about 60 dancers), so it stays personal and facilitates real connection. Whether you’re new to Kizomba or have been putting down roots in this scene for a while now, we’re certain this will be a weekend well spent. Come on over—the fam’s all here! TICKET OPTIONS & PRICING Tier 1 | Earliest Bird: $245 (Only 10 tickets available, closes June 1) Tier 2 | Early Bird: $260 (Only 12 tickets available, closes July 1) Tier 3 | Full Price: $285

description: Come dance in June! Dance starts earlier now! We understand that this is a bit quickly after our last dance but come dance in June. The rest of the summer dances will be early in the month. Pride means rainbows! Wear your rainbows or part of a rainbow this month! We've moved our event to Fridays to encourage more people to come on out and dance with us! We hope this change makes it easier to attend! Doors: 5:45pm Lesson: 6-6:30pm taught by Amie and Patrick (let us know if there's something you want to learn!) small class sizes encourage a more personalized lesson. Social dancing: 6:30-10pm Cost: sliding scale, 5-20$ (no one will be turned away for lack of funds) e-transfer is available. Volunteers: if you would like to volunteer formally for a door shift please contact Patrick or Amie. If you would like to simply show up and be helpful, simply arrive with willing hands at 5:30pm. Accessibility: the building is fully accessible with no steps. you will need to walk slightly uphill if you park in the parking lot Covid: masks are not mandatory. Covid is still around and present though. We support anyone who would like to dance in a mask. Parking: there is a parking lot beside the building just off of townsite Rd. Busses: there is a #1 bus stop right beside the building. Scents: The venue is a scent-free space. Please keep scents to a minimum to consider the space's requirements and people attending's sensitivities Smoking: please just make sure that you are smoking far enough away from the door that the scent doesn't enter the building. What is Fusion Dancing? Fusion is not really a style. It’s an idea, a philosophy, a way of being with ourselves and others, the music and movement, that allows a partner dance to be something unique and different every time. What would happen if you came to a partner dance with no expectations – just to listen and be heard?  What would happen if you and your partner knew how to speak and listen the language of movement beyond patterns?  What would happen if “leading” and “following” didn’t have to do with your gender?  What would happen if the roles of “leading” and “following” blended together, flowing in and out of each other moment to moment?
location: Unitarian Fellowship of Nanaimo Rites of Passage, Unit 1, 595 Townsite Road, Nanaimo

event_name: BC CRABFEST - Serving an Authentic BC CrabBoil
description: Get ready to crack some claws and dive into an authentic Taste of BC Summer's seafood experience! The 3rd BC CrabFest has a new home and is thrilled to announce its 2025 event, taking place on June 29th from 11:00 AM to 7:00 PM at the scenic Ship Point in Victoria’s Inner Harbour. The most delicious part of the festival is the opportunity to purchase a ticket for an irresistible BC Dungeness CrabBoil. Fresh from the docks to the on-site chefs, cooked to perfection and enjoyed harbourside with family and friends. This is the quintessential taste of BC Summertime. The BC Dungeness CrabBoil bucket features the freshest BC Dungeness crab, mussels, prawns/shrimp, potatoes, and corn, all sourced freshly and locally, directly from BC’s hardworking fishing families. This ocean-to-table experience guarantees high quality and ocean friendly sustainability, showcasing the best of what our coastal waters have to offer. Attendees can enjoy a lively Seaside Family Zone, featuring engaging activities for all ages, and all day programming in the Education Marketplace, where guests can dive into sustainable oceans and seafood practices. Reserve your crab and select a one-hour pickup window—then stay and enjoy the festival all day!

description: Class Description This class is for experienced dancers and performers that want to continue to push themselves with more complex techniques. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Monday from 8:00- 9:00pm Must have instructor permission to attend. No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description:
Rehearsal for our Student Bachata Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.

description: Every Friday evening, we're putting on a dance party! Total beginners are always welcome; our drop-in beginner lesson will have you dancing in no time. Neither partner nor experience are required, but pack a spare sense of humour! Following the lesson, the dance features fantastic live music perfect for dancing the night away whether you’re mad about lindy hop, charleston, balboa, or collegiate shag. We've got a regular rotation of bands each month.
location: Dance Victoria, 2750 Quadra St, Victoria, BC V8T 4E8

description: We are excited to bring you dancing the 4th Friday of every month at an all ages venue right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 7:45pm Doors open Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:00pm Salsa lesson Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:00pm- midnight Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. All ages welcome. $15.00 per person + service fee on Eventbrite or cash only at the door. $13 cash for Edelweiss Club members at the door only. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: Victoria Edelweiss Club, 108 Niagara St, Victoria, BC V8V 1E9, Canada

description: Get ready for a night of elegance, rhythm, and summer vibes! Join us for Summer Latin Night, where the dress code is white & gold, the atmosphere is classy, and the music will keep you dancing all night long! Dress Code: Wear your most elegant white & gold outfit and shine on the dance floor! Dance to the best Salsa, Bachata, and Latin beats all night! No partner? No problem! Join our fun intro class at 8:00 PM! Intro Class: 8:00 PM | Social Dance: 8:30 PM - Late. Expect a night filled with: Elegant summer vibes & a welcoming dance community Beautiful white & gold decor Unforgettable Latin music & dancing! Come celebrate summer, style, and Latin passion with us!
location: Ukrainian Cultural Centre, 3277 Douglas St., Victoria, BC

description: Get ready to celebrate the longest day of the year with a night full of Latin rhythms, summer vibes, and nonstop dancing! Salsa | Bachata | Merengue | Latin Beats – all night long! Dress Code: Wear sunset colors – orange, yellow, and red! No partner? No problem! Join our fun intro class at 8:00 PM! Intro Class: 8:00 PM | Social Dance: 8:30 PM - Late Entry: $15 at the door – Bring cash, please! What to Expect: A high-energy Latin dance party Tropical summer decorations & festival vibes A fun and welcoming dance community Come celebrate the official start of summer with us! Let’s dance into the sunset and bring the heat to the dance floor!
location: Ukrainian Cultural Centre, 3277 Douglas St., Victoria, BC

description: To help promote Blues dancing and Blues music in the city, we aim to create a video of Blues dancers dancing to the Fairweather Blues Band. By attending this evening of live music, dancing, and deejayed music, you agree to the following: 1. The video will be filmed for the purpose of promoting the Fairweather Blues Band. 2. The video shall be used by the Fairweather Blues Band without limitation. 3. The video shall be licensed to BConnected Arts Society to promote Shuffle ’n’ Blues. 4. All attendees may be filmed. 5. Not all attendees may be in the final cut. 6. A given song may be repeated to obtain the desired footage. 7. The admission fee will help pay for the venue; profits will be split between the band and BConnected Arts Society. 8. The primary goal of the event is to produce a video. Tickets are $15. Or pay at the door. Schedule: * 7:00 pm - Doors * 7:30 pm - Filming (set 1) * 8:30 pm - Deejay * 8:50 pm - Filming (set 2) * 9:50 pm - Deejay
location: Vancouver Odd Fellows, 1443 W 8th Ave, Vancouver, BC V6H 1C9, Canada
